Reasoning: 
1. cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper explicitly mentions game-theoretic models and presents the pure strategy perfect Bayesian Nash equilibria of the game. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper focuses on deception in network security and presents an application to active network defense. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses game-theoretic models to capture the dynamic and information asymmetric nature of deceptive interactions. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the application of the model to active network defense. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with interactions and communication in network security, which can be seen as a social network.
